From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 16:30:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winepulse: Skip unchanged DualSense mono retargets.

After classifying DualSense Edge `Speaker__sink` endpoints as controller mono
speaker sinks, unplug could attempt to retarget an existing mono stream back to
the exact same Pulse sink while PipeWire/Pulse was tearing that sink down. That
disconnects the stream and waits for a replacement stream that never becomes
ready, hanging Spider-Man Remastered during controller removal.

If the selected mono speaker sink is unchanged and the current stream is still
ready, only refresh the hotplug generations and leave the stream alone. Real
model changes still retarget to the newly connected physical speaker sink.
---
 dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c | 16 ++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+)

diff --git a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
index 55555555555..66666666666 100644
--- a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
+++ b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
@@ -2415,7 +2415,23 @@ static HRESULT pulse_retarget_dualsense_mono_stream(struct pulse_stream *stream)
     if (!(dualsense_speaker = get_dualsense_speaker_sink(NULL, TRUE)))
         return E_FAIL;
 
+    if (!strcmp(stream->device, dualsense_speaker))
+    {
+        if (pulse_stream_ready(stream))
+        {
+            TRACE("Skipping unchanged DualSense mono stream %p on %s.\n",
+                    stream, debugstr_a(dualsense_speaker));
+            stream->haptic_hotplug_generation = g_haptic_hotplug_generation;
+            stream->dualsense_mono_hotplug_generation = g_dualsense_mono_speaker_add_generation;
+            free(dualsense_speaker);
+            return S_OK;
+        }
+
+        free(dualsense_speaker);
+        return E_FAIL;
+    }
+
     TRACE("Retargeting DualSense mono stream %p from %s to %s.\n",
             stream, debugstr_a(stream->device), debugstr_a(dualsense_speaker));
 
     remove_stream_from_period(stream);
